1
00:00:04,690 --> 00:00:09,665
Once one devotee
went as a representative of the Math

2
00:00:09,665 --> 00:00:11,413
to another Math mission

3
00:00:11,413 --> 00:00:16,593
for like on the, say, 
Appearance Day of Saraswati Thakur.

4
00:00:17,403 --> 00:00:20,033
[Spiritual War Scars]

5
00:00:20,423 --> 00:00:24,343
And while there 
he felt as though he’d been abused

6
00:00:25,866 --> 00:00:27,006
by others.

7
00:00:27,061 --> 00:00:30,951
And when he came back,
that news came to Srila Guru Maharaj.

8
00:00:31,758 --> 00:00:35,428
And Guru Maharaja’s interpretation
was interesting.

9
00:00:35,981 --> 00:00:40,201
He said, 
“This is the most noble fight.

10
00:00:41,162 --> 00:00:43,772
Of all the wars, 
of all the battles ...

11
00:00:43,772 --> 00:00:48,177
this is the most noble fight
ever conceived of all time.

12
00:00:50,857 --> 00:00:54,757
Could people ... they are ready to give
their lives for freedom, for independence.

13
00:00:54,761 --> 00:00:58,185
But this mukti—
svarūpena vyavasthitiḥ—

14
00:00:58,185 --> 00:01:01,905
this is the ultimate fight, 
the ultimate struggle, the ultimate battle.”

15
00:01:02,629 --> 00:01:09,499
So Guru Maharaj said, 
“Do you like to come away unscathed?

16
00:01:10,996 --> 00:01:15,616
If there you don’t have a scar
or something,

17
00:01:16,620 --> 00:01:23,270
we may wonder, did you actually 
participate in the battle, in the war?”

18
00:01:23,452 --> 00:01:27,649
I remember as a child
hearing from older men,

19
00:01:27,649 --> 00:01:33,219
who had fought in World War II or what 
Russians called the Great Patriotic War,

20
00:01:33,995 --> 00:01:37,800
and sometimes they’d lift up
their shirt, they’d show you a scar.

21
00:01:37,800 --> 00:01:40,430
And we are like, “Wowwww!”

22
00:01:41,010 --> 00:01:45,601
But if someone didn’t have any scars, 
we were like,

23
00:01:46,281 --> 00:01:48,071
“What were you doing?”

24
00:01:48,071 --> 00:01:49,331
[Laughing]

25
00:01:49,421 --> 00:01:52,701
So Guru Maharaj was saying,
“For this cause,
 

26
00:01:53,381 --> 00:01:56,421
we should be willing 
to take some abuse.”

27
00:01:57,787 --> 00:02:02,417
He was abused, himself—
in Gaudiya Math—

28
00:02:02,417 --> 00:02:06,666
listening so acutely
that one man thought,

29
00:02:06,666 --> 00:02:11,316
“Nobody pays 
that close attention.”

30
00:02:11,316 --> 00:02:14,613
He thought,
“Maybe he is a government spy,

31
00:02:14,613 --> 00:02:20,380
come to spy on us, to see whether or not
we are truly a religious organization

32
00:02:20,380 --> 00:02:23,910
or we have some hidden
political agenda.”

33
00:02:24,680 --> 00:02:27,270
So the next time Guru Maharaj 
came to Saraswati Thakur’s lecture

34
00:02:27,283 --> 00:02:30,833
(he hadn’t joined yet),
the man told him,

35
00:02:30,833 --> 00:02:34,563
“I’m sorry, 
you won’t be allowed.”

36
00:02:34,563 --> 00:02:36,593
Think of that.
 

37
00:02:36,709 --> 00:02:40,359
The Rupanuga-dhara is being told 
by some other devotee,

38
00:02:40,359 --> 00:02:43,279
“You won’t be allowed 
to go to the lecture.”

39
00:02:44,060 --> 00:02:48,170
So Guru Maharaj went for a walk
on the bank of the Ganga.

40
00:02:49,085 --> 00:02:52,345
You should remember 
that the Ganga is also in Calcutta.

41
00:02:53,299 --> 00:02:58,553
And he thought,
“This is intolerable, but I can’t deny

42
00:02:58,553 --> 00:03:02,003
that what I’ve come for,
Saraswati Thakur has,

43
00:03:02,688 --> 00:03:04,568
and what I’ve come for 
is the connection

44
00:03:04,568 --> 00:03:08,158
with the Ultimate Reality,
the Ultimate Substance.

45
00:03:08,358 --> 00:03:12,358
So in deference to that 
I’m willing to tolerate any type of abuse

46
00:03:12,358 --> 00:03:14,738
to maintain my connection.”

47
00:03:15,456 --> 00:03:18,996
So that’s the position 
of a higher devotee

48
00:03:20,227 --> 00:03:25,247
prepared to tolerate anything 
to maintain his connection with ...

49
00:03:26,473 --> 00:03:29,993
That’s one meaning 
of māna-śūnyatā—

50
00:03:29,998 --> 00:03:36,042
the 10: 8, 9, 10 symptoms of bhāva-bhakti,
the absence of ego,

51
00:03:36,042 --> 00:03:40,082
there’s ... 
You can’t insult such a person

52
00:03:40,469 --> 00:03:45,159
because they have no interest 
in maintaining a reputation

53
00:03:45,159 --> 00:03:47,650
or name and fame in this world.

54
00:03:47,650 --> 00:03:49,910
They are only interested

55
00:03:49,910 --> 00:03:53,072
in actual spiritual substance,

56
00:03:53,232 --> 00:03:58,342
and mundane insults
have no affect upon that.

57
00:03:58,926 --> 00:04:03,542
So māna-śūnyatā means
they have the absence of ego assertion

58
00:04:03,542 --> 00:04:05,207
and abhimān

59
00:04:08,337 --> 00:04:11,847
becoming indignant
on their own behalf.

60
00:04:12,777 --> 00:04:14,887
So many things are there.

